Linux 6.6.y for Nuvoton NUC980
==============================

This tree is a Linux 6.6.y LTS port for the Nuvoton NUC980 ARM9 SoC family.
It keeps the upstream Linux kernel layout and adds NUC980 platform support,
device trees, defconfigs, and peripheral drivers used by NUC980 boards.

The base kernel version in this tree is:

    6.6.93

For general Linux kernel documentation, see:

    Documentation/admin-guide/README.rst
    Documentation/process/changes.rst
    https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/


Supported platform
==================

SoC:

    Nuvoton NUC980 series, ARM926EJ-S / ARMv5

Architecture support:

    arch/arm/mach-nuc980/

Main platform Kconfig symbol:

    CONFIG_ARCH_NUC980

Main machine Kconfig symbol:

    CONFIG_MACH_NUC980


Device trees
============

NUC980 device-tree sources are under:

    arch/arm/boot/dts/nuvoton/

The following NUC980 DTBs are built when CONFIG_ARCH_NUC980 is enabled:

    nuc980-dev-v1.0.dtb
    nuc980-iot-v1.0.dtb
    nuc980-iot-g2-v1.0.dtb
    nuc980-iot-g2d-v1.0.dtb
    nuc980-lorag.dtb
    nuc980-eth2uart.dtb
    nuc980-chili.dtb
    nuc980-usb8p-v1.0.dtb

Common SoC definitions are in:

    arch/arm/boot/dts/nuvoton/nuc980.dtsi


Defconfigs
==========

Two NUC980 defconfigs are provided:

    arch/arm/configs/nuc980_defconfig
    arch/arm/configs/nuc980_fmisd_defconfig

Use nuc980_defconfig for the general NUC980 configuration.
Use nuc980_fmisd_defconfig when booting with FMI/SD-oriented storage support.

Both defconfigs currently use an initramfs path of:

    CONFIG_INITRAMFS_SOURCE="../rootfs"

Make sure that path exists relative to the kernel source directory, or change
CONFIG_INITRAMFS_SOURCE before building.


Build
=====

Install an ARM EABI cross compiler, then build from the kernel root.
Set CROSS_COMPILE to match your toolchain prefix.

Example:

    export ARCH=arm
    export CROSS_COMPILE=arm-linux-gnueabi-

    make nuc980_defconfig
    make -j$(nproc) zImage dtbs modules

For the FMI/SD defconfig:

    export ARCH=arm
    export CROSS_COMPILE=arm-linux-gnueabi-

    make nuc980_fmisd_defconfig
    make -j$(nproc) zImage dtbs modules

Main build outputs:

    arch/arm/boot/zImage
    arch/arm/boot/dts/nuvoton/*.dtb
    modules.builtin
    modules.order

To install modules into a root filesystem staging directory:

    make INSTALL_MOD_PATH=/path/to/rootfs modules_install


Boot notes
==========

The provided defconfigs use this default kernel command line:

    root=/dev/ram0 console=ttyS0,115200n8 rdinit=/linuxrc mem=64M

Adjust the command line for your bootloader, memory size, root filesystem, and
selected board DTB.

A typical boot package contains:

    zImage
    one NUC980 board DTB
    initramfs or another root filesystem


NUC980 code map
===============

Important NUC980-specific areas in this tree:

    arch/arm/mach-nuc980/              SoC and machine support
    arch/arm/boot/dts/nuvoton/         NUC980 device trees
    drivers/clk/nuvoton/               NUC980 clock drivers
    drivers/clocksource/timer-nuc980.c NUC980 timer
    drivers/crypto/nuc980-crypto*.c    Crypto engine support
    drivers/dma/nuc980_dma*.c          PDMA support
    drivers/gpio/gpio-nuc980.c         GPIO support
    drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-nuc980-*.c  I2C bus drivers
    drivers/iio/adc/nuc980_nadc.c      ADC support
    drivers/input/                     Keys and touchscreen support
    drivers/media/platform/nuc980-ccap.c
                                      Camera capture support
    drivers/misc/nuc980-*.c            EBI, smart-card, timers, slave helpers
    drivers/mmc/host/nuc980_*.c        FMI/SD support
    drivers/net/can/nuc980_can/        CAN support
    drivers/net/ethernet/nuvoton/      Ethernet MAC support
    drivers/pinctrl/nuvoton/           NUC980 pinctrl support
    drivers/pwm/pwm-nuc980-*.c         PWM support
    drivers/rtc/rtc-nuc980.c           RTC support
    drivers/spi/spi-nuc980-*.c         SPI/QSPI support
    drivers/tty/serial/nuc980_*.c      UART support
    drivers/usb/                       USB host/device support
    drivers/watchdog/nuc980_*.c        WDT/WWDT support
    sound/soc/nuc980/                  ASoC I2S/audio support
    include/linux/platform_data/       NUC980 platform data headers


